Instructions to change the display language

1.Open the Command Palette.
On Windows/Linux, press Ctrl + Shift + P.
On macOS, press Cmd + Shift + P.

2.In the Command Palette, type Configure Display Language.

3.Select the Configure Display Language command from the list.

4.Choose your desired language from the list of locales. For example, select en for English.

After you select the language, VS Code will prompt you to restart to apply the change. Accept the prompt, and the editor will reload in your chosen language. 